transcript: I remember taking a class called entrepreneurship uh when I was at vanderbelt none of the things that I had in that class at all had anything to do with what I do today or what I needed when I actually started a first business the idea of a business model A business plan and all of these fancier things basically none of those have happened with every business I've started for the most part it was I think people would buy this what do we think we can make it for how much will they buy it for and then how do we get people to give us money
